# Summary
Microscope is a feature in Amplitude that allows users to analyze specific data points in charts by hovering over them, providing options like viewing user streams, showing user paths, creating cohorts, and launching session replays. It enables detailed inspection of individual user behaviors and supports creating targeted guides, surveys, and experiments directly from chart data points.

